<chapter>
  <title><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Equity_Options"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> Module</title>

  <para role="TEXT">The <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml"
  xpointer="ent_Equity_Options" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" />
  module enables you, on behalf of your company, to arrange equity
  options.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">For basic features common to all modules, such as basic terminology
  and the use of lists and forms, see chapter
  <emphasis>Introduction</emphasis>. For descriptions of functions, see
  chapter <emphasis>Functions</emphasis>.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">This chapter gives detailed descriptions of the input forms used by
  this module, and describes any features specific to this module.</para>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Equity Options</title>

    <para role="TEXT">Equity options are securities that give the holder the right (but
    not the obligation) to buy or sell a specified number of stock shares, at
    a specified price, for a certain (limited) time period. Typically one
    option equals 100 shares of stock.</para>

    <para role="TEXT"><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_applisump"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> supports both American and
    European style vanilla options. It also provides the ability to price
    foreign currency equity options.</para>
  </section>

