      <section role="ITEM">
        <title>Single Barrier</title>

        <informaltable frame="all">
          <tgroup cols="2">
            <colspec colname="column-1" colwidth="2357*" />

            <colspec colname="column-2" colwidth="6499*" />

            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"> <emphasis
                role="bold">Field</emphasis> </para></entry>

                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"> <emphasis
                role="bold">Description</emphasis> </para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry colsep="1"
                rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Type</guilabel></para></entry>

                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Type of the barrier to be
                applied to the swap option. Choices are:</para><para role="TEXT"><emphasis
                role="bold">None</emphasis> â€“ No
                barrier.</para><para role="TEXT"><emphasis
                role="bold">Up-and-in</emphasis> - An up-and-in call comes
                with a barrier set above the current spot FX (the upper
                barrier). The option becomes a vanilla call when the
                underlying FX crosses the barrier. If the barrier is never
                crossed during the life of the option, it expires with a
                payoff of zero.</para><para role="TEXT"><emphasis
                role="bold">Up-and-out</emphasis> - An up-and-out call comes
                with a barrier set above the current spot FX (the upper
                barrier). The option becomes worthless (out) if the barrier is
                crossed during the life of the option. If the barrier is never
                crossed during the life of the option, it expires with a
                payoff of zero.</para><para role="TEXT"><emphasis
                role="bold">Down-and-in</emphasis> - A down-and-in call comes
                with a barrier set below the current spot FX (the upper
                barrier). The option becomes a vanilla call when the
                underlying FX crosses the barrier. If the barrier is never
                crossed during the life of the option, it expires with a
                payoff of zero.</para><para role="TEXT"><emphasis
                role="bold">Down-and-out</emphasis> - An up-and-out call comes
                with a barrier set below the current spot FX (the upper
                barrier). The option becomes worthless (out) if the barrier is
                crossed during the life of the option. If the barrier is never
                crossed during the life of the option, it expires with a
                payoff of zero.</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guibutton>Add
                Barrier</guibutton></para></entry>

                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Click this button to open
                the Add Barrier window.</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">Rebate Type</para></entry>

                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">The date at which the
                rebate is paid:</para><para role="TEXT"><emphasis role="bold">None â€“
                </emphasis>No rebate is received.</para><para role="TEXT"><emphasis
                role="bold">Instant rebate â€“ </emphasis>The rebate is received
                when the equity option crosses or touches a
                barrier.</para><para role="TEXT"><emphasis role="bold">Expiry Rebate â€“
                </emphasis>The rebate is received when the equity option
                expires, regardless of the date on which it crosses or touches
                a barrier.</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Rebate
                Amount</guilabel></para></entry>

                <entry colsep="1" rowsep="1"><para role="TEXT">The amount received when
                the rebate becomes invalid. In the first field, specify the
                currency; click the magnifying glass icon to select. In the
                second field, specify the rebate amount.</para></entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </informaltable>
